Quickstrike:




Quickstrike watched the outside, with his mismatched arms crossed. 
The Predacons hadn't returned even after a couple of mega-cycles. He 
beat them here. He was probably better off walking back. Something 
must have happened. But he didn't care. There was a rule, among many 
rules he learned: Only the strong survive.

He leaned on the entrance, ankles crossed, and putting weight onto 
his shoulder. The ambient was silent and the clouds drifted slowly 
past.

He shook his head. The peaceful ambient made him feel strange. His 
bright crimson optics glowed in agitation. He walked off to the 
bunker where the ohers might be.
